## üîπ 4. Rest Syntax
Rest syntax collects remaining properties into a new object.
```javascript
const user = { name: 'Alice', age: 25, role: 'Admin' };
const { name, ...rest } = user;
console.log(name); // Alice
console.log(rest); // { age: 25, role: 'Admin' }
```

