## üîπ 5. Shallow Copy Warning
Spread creates a shallow copy. Nested objects are still references.
```javascript
const obj = { a: 1, nested: { b: 2 } };
const copy = { ...obj };
copy.nested.b = 99;
console.log(obj.nested.b); // 99 (nested object changed)
```

